A weathered stone wheel half-buried in moss and ferns, with five distinct segments showing the gradual transformation of ancient mechanical gears slowly morphing into glowing circuit patterns, then into organic vines reclaiming the technology. The scene is set in a misty forest clearing at golden hour, with soft light filtering through towering trees. Small fireflies drift around the wheel, some appearing digital and pixelated while others are natural. The mood is melancholic yet peaceful, suggesting the eternal cycle of technological rise and fall. Fallen autumn leaves in rust and amber tones scatter around the base, while new green shoots emerge from cracks in the stone. Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, dreamy atmospheric perspective, and intricate hand-drawn details in the mechanical and natural elements.
